{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UYhhezhJGF5bCBDzAmYMXJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 16.6: Story Flow Execution\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the workflow engine to execute `story_flow` for each story within an epic,\n9\tso that the hierarchical flow model drives story-level execution.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** a workflow with `story_flow: [implement, verify, loop: [retry, verify], telemetry]`, **when** the engine processes an epic's stories, **then** each story runs through the complete story_flow pipeline in order (implement, verify, loop block, telemetry). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** a story_flow containing a `telemetry` null task after the loop block, **when** a story's verify passes (loop exits early) or the loop exhausts max iterations, **then** the telemetry null task still executes after the loop completes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** a story_flow with `loop: [retry, verify]`, **when** the loop executes, **then** existing loop semantics are preserved: max iterations, circuit breaker evaluation, early exit on pass verdict. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** a workflow with only `flow:` (no `story_flow`, no `execution`), **when** the engine runs, **then** behavior is identical to current behavior (backward compat). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** a workflow with both `story_flow` and `execution` sections, **when** the engine initializes, **then** it reads `storyFlow` from the resolved workflow instead of `flow`, and uses the `execution` config for engine-level settings. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** a resolved workflow where `storyFlow` is non-empty but `flow` is the legacy fallback, **when** the engine logs the workflow name, **then** it derives the name from `storyFlow` (not `flow`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n26\t\n27\t- [ ] Task 1: Switch `executeWorkflow()` to use `storyFlow` instead of `flow` (AC: #1, #4, #5)\n28\t  - [ ] In `executeWorkflow()` (line ~1212), change `config.workflow.flow` to `config.workflow.storyFlow`\n29\t  - [ ] `storyFlow` is already populated by `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` — for legacy `flow:` workflows, `storyFlow` contains the same steps as `flow` (backward compat guaranteed by story 16-1)\n30\t  - [ ] Update the `workflow_name` derivation (line ~1172) to use `storyFlow` instead of `flow`\n31\t  - [ ] Verify that `ResolvedWorkflow.flow` is still populated (it is — keep it for any other consumers)\n32\t\n33\t- [ ] Task 2: Verify loop semantics are preserved under `storyFlow` (AC: #3)\n34\t  - [ ] The `executeLoopBlock()` function already handles `LoopBlock` steps — confirm it works identically when reached via `storyFlow` iteration\n35\t  - [ ] Loop max iterations, circuit breaker, and early-exit-on-pass must behave the same\n36\t  - [ ] Write a test: story_flow with loop block executes the loop with max iterations respected\n37\t\n38\t- [ ] Task 3: Verify telemetry null task executes after loop (AC: #2)\n39\t  - [ ] The telemetry task appears after the loop block in `story_flow: [implement, verify, loop: [retry, verify], telemetry]`\n40\t  - [ ] After the loop block completes (pass, max-iterations, or circuit-breaker), the engine continues to the next step (`telemetry`)\n41\t  - [ ] Write a test: story_flow `[implement, verify, loop: [...], telemetry]` — telemetry handler is called after loop completes\n42\t  - [ ] Edge case: if loop triggers `halted = true` (circuit breaker), does the engine skip telemetry? Document and test the behavior.\n43\t\n44\t- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests for storyFlow execution (AC: #1–#6)\n45\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with `story_flow` executes steps in order\n46\t  - [ ] Test: workflow with only `flow` (legacy) still works identically\n47\t  - [ ] Test: `workflow_name` is derived from `storyFlow` steps\n48\t  - [ ] Test: story_flow with loop block preserves loop semantics\n49\t  - [ ] Test: story_flow with null task after loop executes the null task\n50\t  - [ ] Test: story_flow with multiple per-story tasks iterates all work items for each task\n51\t\n52\t- [ ] Task 5: Verify backward compatibility end-to-end (AC: #4)\n53\t  - [ ] Run the full test suite — all existing tests that use `flow:` must pass unchanged\n54\t  - [ ] The `ResolvedWorkflow.flow` field remains populated (no removal)\n55\t  - [ ] Any code that reads `workflow.flow` directly still works\n56\t\n57\t## Dev Notes\n58\t\n59\t### Architecture Constraints\n60\t\n61\t- **Architecture Decision 4** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Workflow YAML gains `execution`, `story_flow`, `epic_flow`. Existing flat `flow:` is syntactic sugar for `story_flow:` with default execution config. Backward compatibility is mandatory.\n62\t- **Architecture Data Flow**: `Workflow YAML -> hierarchical-flow parser -> execution config + storyFlow + epicFlow -> workflow-engine (per lane) -> execute storyFlow for each story`\n63\t- The `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` function (story 16-1) already normalizes `flow:` into `storyFlow`. The engine just needs to read `storyFlow` instead of `flow`.\n64\t\n65\t### Key Files to Modify\n66\t\n67\t| File | Change |\n68\t|------|--------|\n69\t| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | Change `config.workflow.flow` to `config.workflow.storyFlow` in `executeWorkflow()`. Update `workflow_name` derivation. |\n70\t\n71\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n72\t\n73\t| File | Why |\n74\t|------|-----|\n75\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` — produces `storyFlow` from `flow:` or `story_flow:`. Already done in 16-1. |\n76\t| `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` | `ResolvedWorkflow` interface — has both `flow` and `storyFlow` fields. |\n77\t| `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` | Null task handler registry — telemetry handler registered at module load. |\n78\t| `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` | `writeTelemetryEntry()` — the telemetry null task handler. |\n79\t| `src/lib/__tests__/null-task-engine.test.ts` | Existing tests for null task execution in the engine — verify they still pass. |\n80\t| `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` | Existing engine tests — all must pass unchanged. |\n81\t\n82\t### Critical Implementation Detail\n83\t\n84\tThe change is intentionally minimal. `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` (story 16-1) already does the heavy lifting:\n85\t- Legacy `flow:` workflows get `storyFlow = flow` (same steps)\n86\t- Hierarchical `story_flow:` workflows get `storyFlow` directly from YAML\n87\t\n88\tThe engine change is essentially: `for (const step of config.workflow.flow)` -> `for (const step of config.workflow.storyFlow)`.\n89\t\n90\tThe risk is in any code path that reads `config.workflow.flow` directly. Grep the codebase for `workflow.flow` and `\\.flow\\b` to find all consumers before changing.\n91\t\n92\t### Previous Story (16-5) Intelligence\n93\t\n94\t- 16-5 added coverage deduplication: `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()` in `workflow-engine.ts`, wired into `dispatchTaskWithResult()`. Coverage skip logic in runner.\n95\t- 16-4 added `propagateVerifyFlags()` in `workflow-engine.ts` — called after every `dispatchTaskWithResult()`.\n96\t- 16-3 added `telemetry-writer.ts` and the `telemetry` null task handler in the registry.\n97\t- 16-2 added `executeNullTask()` in `workflow-engine.ts` and the null task registry.\n98\t- 16-1 added `hierarchical-flow.ts` with `resolveHierarchicalFlow()`, `HierarchicalFlow` interface, `ExecutionConfig`.\n99\t- Code review (16-5) caught: duplicate type definitions, missing parameters, misleading JSDoc. Be precise.\n100\t- All 4768 tests pass as of 16-5.\n101\t\n102\t### Edge Cases\n103\t\n104\t- **Circuit breaker halts during loop**: If the loop sets `halted = true` via circuit breaker, the `for` loop over `storyFlow` steps will `break` — telemetry after the loop will NOT run. This matches current `flow:` behavior. Document this as expected.\n105\t- **`max-iterations` phase after loop**: If loop sets `state.phase = 'max-iterations'`, the engine sets `halted = true` — again, telemetry won't run. Same as current behavior.\n106\t- **Empty `storyFlow`**: If `storyFlow` is `[]` (no steps), the engine completes immediately. This is valid and matches `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` returning `[]` for missing flows.\n107\t\n108\t### Project Structure Notes\n109\t\n110\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n111\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `__tests__/` directories\n112\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n113\t- Build: `npm run build`\n114\t- Test: `npm test`\n115\t\n116\t### References\n117\t\n118\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 16.6]\n119\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 4 — Hierarchical Flow Model]\n120\t- [Source: src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts — resolveHierarchicalFlow(), HierarchicalFlow interface]\n121\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — ResolvedWorkflow interface (flow, storyFlow, epicFlow)]\n122\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — executeWorkflow(), executeLoopBlock(), executeNullTask()]\n123\t- [Source: src/lib/null-task-registry.ts — getNullTask(), registerNullTask()]\n124\t- [Source: src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts — writeTelemetryEntry()]\n125\t\n126\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n127\t## Verification Requirements\n128\t\n129\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-6-story-flow-execution-proof.md)\n130\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n131\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n132\t\n133\t## Documentation Requirements\n134\t\n135\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n136\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-6-story-flow-execution.md\n137\t\n138\t## Testing Requirements\n139\t\n140\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n141\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n142\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n143\t\n144\t## Dev Agent Record\n145\t\n146\t### Agent Model Used\n147\t\n148\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n149\t\n150\t### Debug Log References\n151\t\n152\t### Completion Notes List\n153\t\n154\t### File List\n155\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e648a229-0e5b-4ea4-9861-593afdfcccd5","uuid":"b414466b-ff24-42c7-a773-825d1e6e8934","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:56:17.296Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-6-story-flow-execution.md","content":"# Story 16.6: Story Flow Execution\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want the workflow engine to execute `story_flow` for each story within an epic,\nso that the hierarchical flow model drives story-level execution.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a workflow with `story_flow: [implement, verify, loop: [retry, verify], telemetry]`, **when** the engine processes an epic's stories, **then** each story runs through the complete story_flow pipeline in order (implement, verify, loop block, telemetry). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** a story_flow containing a `telemetry` null task after the loop block, **when** a story's verify passes (loop exits early) or the loop exhausts max iterations, **then** the telemetry null task still executes after the loop completes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a story_flow with `loop: [retry, verify]`, **when** the loop executes, **then** existing loop semantics are preserved: max iterations, circuit breaker evaluation, early exit on pass verdict. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** a workflow with only `flow:` (no `story_flow`, no `execution`), **when** the engine runs, **then** behavior is identical to current behavior (backward compat). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** a workflow with both `story_flow` and `execution` sections, **when** the engine initializes, **then** it reads `storyFlow` from the resolved workflow instead of `flow`, and uses the `execution` config for engine-level settings. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a resolved workflow where `storyFlow` is non-empty but `flow` is the legacy fallback, **when** the engine logs the workflow name, **then** it derives the name from `storyFlow` (not `flow`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Switch `executeWorkflow()` to use `storyFlow` instead of `flow` (AC: #1, #4, #5)\n  - [ ] In `executeWorkflow()` (line ~1212), change `config.workflow.flow` to `config.workflow.storyFlow`\n  - [ ] `storyFlow` is already populated by `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` — for legacy `flow:` workflows, `storyFlow` contains the same steps as `flow` (backward compat guaranteed by story 16-1)\n  - [ ] Update the `workflow_name` derivation (line ~1172) to use `storyFlow` instead of `flow`\n  - [ ] Verify that `ResolvedWorkflow.flow` is still populated (it is — keep it for any other consumers)\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Verify loop semantics are preserved under `storyFlow` (AC: #3)\n  - [ ] The `executeLoopBlock()` function already handles `LoopBlock` steps — confirm it works identically when reached via `storyFlow` iteration\n  - [ ] Loop max iterations, circuit breaker, and early-exit-on-pass must behave the same\n  - [ ] Write a test: story_flow with loop block executes the loop with max iterations respected\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Verify telemetry null task executes after loop (AC: #2)\n  - [ ] The telemetry task appears after the loop block in `story_flow: [implement, verify, loop: [retry, verify], telemetry]`\n  - [ ] After the loop block completes (pass, max-iterations, or circuit-breaker), the engine continues to the next step (`telemetry`)\n  - [ ] Write a test: story_flow `[implement, verify, loop: [...], telemetry]` — telemetry handler is called after loop completes\n  - [ ] Edge case: if loop triggers `halted = true` (circuit breaker), does the engine skip telemetry? Document and test the behavior.\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests for storyFlow execution (AC: #1–#6)\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with `story_flow` executes steps in order\n  - [ ] Test: workflow with only `flow` (legacy) still works identically\n  - [ ] Test: `workflow_name` is derived from `storyFlow` steps\n  - [ ] Test: story_flow with loop block preserves loop semantics\n  - [ ] Test: story_flow with null task after loop executes the null task\n  - [ ] Test: story_flow with multiple per-story tasks iterates all work items for each task\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Verify backward compatibility end-to-end (AC: #4)\n  - [ ] Run the full test suite — all existing tests that use `flow:` must pass unchanged\n  - [ ] The `ResolvedWorkflow.flow` field remains populated (no removal)\n  - [ ] Any code that reads `workflow.flow` directly still works\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **Architecture Decision 4** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Workflow YAML gains `execution`, `story_flow`, `epic_flow`. Existing flat `flow:` is syntactic sugar for `story_flow:` with default execution config. Backward compatibility is mandatory.\n- **Architecture Data Flow**: `Workflow YAML -> hierarchical-flow parser -> execution config + storyFlow + epicFlow -> workflow-engine (per lane) -> execute storyFlow for each story`\n- The `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` function (story 16-1) already normalizes `flow:` into `storyFlow`. The engine just needs to read `storyFlow` instead of `flow`.\n\n### Key Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | Change `config.workflow.flow` to `config.workflow.storyFlow` in `executeWorkflow()`. Update `workflow_name` derivation. |\n\n### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n\n| File | Why |\n|------|-----|\n| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` — produces `storyFlow` from `flow:` or `story_flow:`. Already done in 16-1. |\n| `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` | `ResolvedWorkflow` interface — has both `flow` and `storyFlow` fields. |\n| `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` | Null task handler registry — telemetry handler registered at module load. |\n| `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` | `writeTelemetryEntry()` — the telemetry null task handler. |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/null-task-engine.test.ts` | Existing tests for null task execution in the engine — verify they still pass. |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` | Existing engine tests — all must pass unchanged. |\n\n### Critical Implementation Detail\n\nThe change is intentionally minimal. `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` (story 16-1) already does the heavy lifting:\n- Legacy `flow:` workflows get `storyFlow = flow` (same steps)\n- Hierarchical `story_flow:` workflows get `storyFlow` directly from YAML\n\nThe engine change is essentially: `for (const step of config.workflow.flow)` -> `for (const step of config.workflow.storyFlow)`.\n\nThe risk is in any code path that reads `config.workflow.flow` directly. Grep the codebase for `workflow.flow` and `\\.flow\\b` to find all consumers before changing.\n\n### Previous Story (16-5) Intelligence\n\n- 16-5 added coverage deduplication: `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()` in `workflow-engine.ts`, wired into `dispatchTaskWithResult()`. Coverage skip logic in runner.\n- 16-4 added `propagateVerifyFlags()` in `workflow-engine.ts` — called after every `dispatchTaskWithResult()`.\n- 16-3 added `telemetry-writer.ts` and the `telemetry` null task handler in the registry.\n- 16-2 added `executeNullTask()` in `workflow-engine.ts` and the null task registry.\n- 16-1 added `hierarchical-flow.ts` with `resolveHierarchicalFlow()`, `HierarchicalFlow` interface, `ExecutionConfig`.\n- Code review (16-5) caught: duplicate type definitions, missing parameters, misleading JSDoc. Be precise.\n- All 4768 tests pass as of 16-5.\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n- **Circuit breaker halts during loop**: If the loop sets `halted = true` via circuit breaker, the `for` loop over `storyFlow` steps will `break` — telemetry after the loop will NOT run. This matches current `flow:` behavior. Document this as expected.\n- **`max-iterations` phase after loop**: If loop sets `state.phase = 'max-iterations'`, the engine sets `halted = true` — again, telemetry won't run. Same as current behavior.\n- **Empty `storyFlow`**: If `storyFlow` is `[]` (no steps), the engine completes immediately. This is valid and matches `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` returning `[]` for missing flows.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n- Tests: vitest, colocated in `__tests__/` directories\n- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n- Build: `npm run build`\n- Test: `npm test`\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 16.6]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 4 — Hierarchical Flow Model]\n- [Source: src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts — resolveHierarchicalFlow(), HierarchicalFlow interface]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — ResolvedWorkflow interface (flow, storyFlow, epicFlow)]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — executeWorkflow(), executeLoopBlock(), executeNullTask()]\n- [Source: src/lib/null-task-registry.ts — getNullTask(), registerNullTask()]\n- [Source: src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts — writeTelemetryEntry()]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-6-story-flow-execution-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-6-story-flow-execution.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n","numLines":155,"startLine":1,"totalLines":155}}}
